definition.value: A glycosyl glycoside formed by glucose and fructose units joined by an acetal oxygen bridge from hemiacetal of glucose to the hemiketal of the fructose.
A pyridinium ion that is L-alanine in which a methyl hydrogen is replaced by a 3,4-dioxidopyridinium-1-yl group.
A ribose bisphosphate that consists of D-ribose having two monophosphate groups at the 1- and 5-positions.
